1
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:01,400
Xu Xiao.

2
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:05,800
How is it?

3
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:06,400
I got it.

4
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,050
Are we almost there?

5
00:01:36,039 --> 00:01:36,970
It's just ahead.

6
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:38,120
Okay.

7
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:53,370
Let's go.

8
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:02,340
Brother Hu.

9
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,139
Brother Hu.

10
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,240
Xu Xiao.

11
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,010
What are you here to burn today?

12
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:35,600
Okay.

13
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,000
I'll squeeze you in.

14
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,120
This is a gas kiln.

15
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:45,320
It's for general household use.

16
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:46,000
Large porcelain factories

17
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,530
usually won't fire a single item just for you.

18
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:54,320
Brother Hu started working at such a young age.

19
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,960
It's his family's business.

20
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:57,480
In these family workshops,

21
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:58,960
many children grow up following their parents

22
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,240
and working alongside them.

23
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:03,440
Their skills aren't necessarily worse than those of ceramics students.

24
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,970
As expected of Jingdezhen.

25
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:08,930
It's a place where even three-year-olds know how to play with clay.

26
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:22,010
Master Pang, let go.

27
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:25,300
Is that polite?

28
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,660
Is that polite?

29
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,280
Boss.

30
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,440
Xiaocen.

31
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,040
Are you okay?

32
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,780
Lord Pang has princess syndrome.

33
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,120
He's always trying to get my attention.

34
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,360
Every now and then, he takes

35
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,560
some shiny things from my desk.

36
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,680
Look, he took my Southern Red Agate again.

37
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:45,940
It's become a treasure pavilion in here.

38
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:47,770
Come, come, have a seat.

39
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,200
Okay.

40
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:51,720
This is the newly arrived pre-Qingming Longjing tea.

41
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,579
Let's have a taste.

42
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,640
Boss.

43
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,520
What is this?

44
00:03:59,079 --> 00:04:00,320
Isn't this the one at our entrance,

45
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,360
our best-selling

46
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:03,020
Hundred Family Surnames cup?

47
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,890
The unglazed body looks like this.

48
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,200
It is fate that we met.

49
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,200
I'll give you one.

50
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:09,770
This one.

51
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:11,360
This one is not bad.

52
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,560
The shape is regular.

53
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:14,290
Tonight,

54
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:17,079
I'll find someone to write your character 'Cen' on it.

55
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:17,920
It'll be put into the kiln tomorrow.

56
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:20,250
I'll deliver it to your home the day after.

57
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,160
Boss.

58
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,080
Can I

59
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:25,420
write this character myself?

60
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:26,500
Write it yourself?

61
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:40,080
Boss,

62
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,600
I'm done writing.

63
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,320
Let me see.

64
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,760
Your handwriting is pretty good.

65
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:49,880
This Slender Gold style

66
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:51,010
has some character.

67
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,840
Xiaocen, your handwriting...

68
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:54,320
For handwriting like this,

69
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,440
if I hired someone outside to do it,

70
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:56,500
it would cost a lot.

71
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:00,800
Xiaocen.

72
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:02,560
You know what?

73
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,320
I really envy you young people.

74
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:05,940
Do you know why?

75
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,800
Because you have plenty of time.

76
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,400
Time is money.

77
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:12,860
Look at Xu Xiao.

78
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,480
He spends a lot of his time here,

79
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,440
turning what would be meaningless time

80
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:19,040
into something meaningful.

81
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:24,570
Are you interested in a part-time job?

82
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,570
A part-time job?

83
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:27,520
For every cup,

84
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,960
I'll give you 5 yuan.

85
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:31,320
Don't underestimate this 5 yuan.

86
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:33,520
We can produce over ten items a day here.

87
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:35,010
That's 60 or 70 yuan.

88
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:35,880
Add it up over a month.

89
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:37,159
Imagine how much that is.

90
00:05:37,159 --> 00:05:37,640
Right?

91
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,200
Most importantly,

92
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,860
the money isn't what matters.

93
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:43,440
Xu works here every day,

94
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,840
and he gets quite lonely.

95
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:47,040
You two could keep each other company.

96
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,840
You guys are classmates, right?

97
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,440
What are you talking about?

98
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,000
Xu!

99
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,440
You're right on time.

100
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,600
Xiaocen is going to work here.

101
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,180
Come on, meet your new colleague.

102
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,960
I never thought

103
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:06,560
I could be of use.

104
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:09,380
I can't believe someone hired me.

105
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:11,410
Don't sell yourself short.

106
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,260
You're very talented.

107
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,280
Actually,

108
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:22,480
I've always thought of myself as pretty ordinary.

109
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,960
Just like

110
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,920
a little dirt mound by the roadside.

111
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,700
You think you're a little dirt mound,

112
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,520
but actually,

113
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,580
you're unrefined kaolin.

114
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:34,200
Kaolin.

115
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,080
Right.

116
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,360
Isn't it still just clay?

117
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,159
No.

118
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,200
It is the best

119
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,600
clay for making ceramics.

120
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,060
Sister.

121
00:06:48,159 --> 00:06:48,880
Xiaoxing, it's your turn.

122
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:49,480
Hurry.

123
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,700
What are you doing?

124
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:53,370
Let's go.

125
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:54,760
What's wrong?

126
00:06:58,880 --> 00:06:59,720
This is my classmate.

127
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,480
This is my brother-in-law.

128
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,740
What brother-in-law?

129
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:02,560
This... this is...

130
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,620
I am her classmate.

131
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,680
My name is Xu Xiao.

132
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,640
It's too late today,

133
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,800
so I brought her back.

134
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,480
Then you are the future brother-in-law.

135
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,880
Brother-in-law, you'd better run.

136
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:11,680
My aunt must be watching from upstairs.

137
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,960
It'll be trouble if she sees you.

138
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,440
Xiaoxing can take me back.

139
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:15,680
You can go.

140
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:16,960
Good night. Good night.

141
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:17,520
Let's go.

142
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:18,280
Brother-in-law.

143
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:18,960
Good night.

144
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:21,100
What are you talking about? Let's go.

145
00:07:28,520 --> 00:07:29,050
Xiaocen.

146
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,250
Xiaocen.

147
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:31,520
Hello.

148
00:07:32,159 --> 00:07:33,400
What are you guys going to do?

149
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:34,880
We... we're going fishing.

150
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:35,320
Right.

151
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,320
Fishing.

152
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:38,600
Isn't fishing banned at school?

153
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:41,330
It's fine. We'll just avoid the security guards.

154
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:43,680
Bye.

155
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,159
Bye. We're leaving.

156
00:07:44,159 --> 00:07:44,640
Bye.

157
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:58,490
You're here.

158
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:01,760
Why are you here?

159
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,940
The four of them occasionally swim over.

160
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,460
I'm going to feed them.

161
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,340
Have a seat.

162
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:31,700
You really like it.

163
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:39,500
This is the first piece of pottery

164
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:41,640
I've fired in my life.

165
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:43,880
No,

166
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:45,920
we fired.

167
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,320
If you like it,

168
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,060
it's yours.

169
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:56,840
Really?

170
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,320
Thank you.

171
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:04,820
No problem.

172
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,840
You two, stop right there!

173
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,080
Boss, we were wrong.

174
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:10,480
Stop!

175
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,240
Li Zhuoting, hurry up!

176
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,640
Wang Lin, why are you calling my name?

177
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,040
Stop!

178
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,840
Why didn't you bring me to get ice pops?

179
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,300
Who knew if you wanted one.

180
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,720
When mentioning the Tang Dynasty,

181
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:29,480
most people will think of Tang Sancai.

182
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:32,280
Like the well-known Tang Sancai porcelain horse.

183
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:32,920
However,

184
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:34,600
Tang Sancai

185
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:37,480
is not recorded in history.

186
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,820
In the very beginning,

187
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:42,320
there were no actual objects handed down.

188
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,160
Until when?

189
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,040
In the late Qing Dynasty,

190
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,920
it was finally found in Tang Dynasty tombs

191
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,980
that this kind of porcelain existed.

192
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,400
Therefore,

193
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:55,240
Wang Lin said we should go play a LARP game after class.

194
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:57,440
Ask Wu Jing if she wants to go.

195
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,120
Later on,

196
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:01,600
with the continuous efforts

197
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,360
and excavation of archaeologists,

198
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:03,820
Wu Jing.

199
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:05,480
Wu Jing.

200
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,440
Tang Sancai was discovered.

201
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:09,540
From where?

202
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:13,560
From ordinary residences to temple ruins.

203
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,660
People gradually came to know

204
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,740
about Tang Sancai.

205
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:19,360
Wang Lin, Li Zhuoting.

206
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:22,360
Are you two taking a culture class

207
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,680
or a dance class?

208
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:26,480
Tang Sancai is actually a type of

209
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,000
colorful pottery.

210
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:29,680
Class is over.

211
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,600
Yuexin, are you going?

212
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,120
Yan Xue.

213
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,000
I'll go if you go.

214
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:36,600
Let's go.

215
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:37,960
We don't have classes this afternoon anyway.

216
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:38,690
That's true.

217
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:39,480
Xiaoyi.

218
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,160
Wanna go play a murder mystery game?

219
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:41,680
Sure.

220
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:44,240
Xiaocen.

221
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,120
We are going to play a murder mystery game this afternoon.

222
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,180
Do you want to come?

223
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,360
I've never played a murder mystery game before.

224
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,160
You don't need to know how to play.

225
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,440
The DM (host) will guide us through the process.

226
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,570
Just follow my lead.

227
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:56,040
DM (host)?

228
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:56,760
Come on.

229
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:58,720
You didn't come sing karaoke with us last time.

230
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,250
Let's go have fun together.

231
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,160
Bye.

232
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:03,720
Bye.

233
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:04,880
I like that too.

234
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:05,560
It's my favorite.

235
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,160
And Lonely God.

236
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,400
I want five packs.

237
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:08,080
Okay.

238
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,140
You said it.

239
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,250
Let's introduce ourselves first.

240
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:22,000
I'm Mo Sanfeng of the Embroidered Uniform Guard.

241
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:24,480
Hello, everyone. I'm Su Ying'er.

242
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,760
Hello, everyone. I am Cuiwen, a maid in the prince's mansion.

243
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:32,090
Hello, everyone. I am Princess Xiangyue.

244
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:35,120
Hello, everyone. I am Chen, the butler of the prince's mansion.

245
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:38,200
I am Liu Rushuang, a famous courtesan in the capital.

246
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,930
This role suits you perfectly.

247
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:43,480
Hello, everyone. I am Lin, the chief eunuch.

248
00:11:59,000 --> 00:11:59,860
It's your turn.

249
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:04,040
I am... I am Lin, the chief eunuch.

250
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,880
I was at the prince's mansion that day.

251
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:11,160
Tell us more.

252
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:12,440
What were you doing there?

253
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,080
Say a little more.

254
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:13,680
Exactly.

255
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:14,880
Do you have any clues?

256
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,520
When I was young, I lived in the desert.

257
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:23,600
I passed by Liu Rushuang's room.

258
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,320
What was she saying?

259
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:28,040
Although Shazhou in the Tang Dynasty was a prosperous place,

260
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,480
there were years of famine.

261
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,880
Xiaocen, Xiaocen.

262
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,560
Just summarize it yourself

263
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,620
and say it out loud.

264
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,020
I might not summarize it well.

265
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,840
Basically, I...

266
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:43,090
I was just at the prince's mansion doing nothing.

267
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:23,680
I was in the desert when I was little.

268
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:25,140
What is she talking about?

269
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:25,720
I don't know either.

270
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:28,680
I just passed by Liu Rushuang's room.

271
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:56,920
I feel a bit addicted.

272
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:57,980
It's just us today.

273
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,400
Didn't you invite Xiaocen?

274
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,360
She doesn't even know how to play.

275
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,480
Let's pick a scary one today.

276
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:01,840
How about it?

277
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,440
All right.

278
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,260
That works.

279
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:19,920
Is this okay?

280
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,290
Pretty much.

281
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,440
Just put it aside.

282
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,640
I'll handle the rest.

283
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,360
Why don't you take a rest?

284
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,120
You're awake.

285
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,800
How long did I sleep?

286
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:49,760
Not long.

287
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,160
It's already 5:00.

288
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:58,800
I'm sorry.

289
